 The source of the virus can be from natural epidemics such as Ebola, 

00:04:32.846 --> 00:04:34.826
 Or it could be biological terrorism. 

00:04:34.826 --> 00:04:39.754
 There are things that can make the situation much worse. 

00:04:39.754 --> 00:04:45.475
 In fact, let's look at a model of a virus spreading through the air, 

00:04:45.475 --> 00:04:49.070
 Like the Spanish flu that appeared in 1918. 

00:04:49.630 --> 00:04:51.560
 This is what can happen. 

00:04:51.560 --> 00:04:55.558
 It can spread all over the world very, very quickly. 

00:04:55.558 --> 00:05:00.683
 And you can see more than 30 million deaths from this epidemic. 

00:05:00.683 --> 00:05:02.496
 So this is a serious problem. 

00:05:02.496 --> 00:05:04.257
 We have to take care of it. 

00:05:04.257 --> 00:05:08.692
 But in fact, we can build a very good response system. 

00:05:08.692 --> 00:05:13.836
 We have the advantages of all science and technology that we talked about. 

00:05:13.836 --> 00:05:14.883
 We have cell phones 

00:05:14.883 --> 00:05:18.140
 To obtain information from the public and to communicate it with them. 

00:05:18.140 --> 00:05:22.319
 We have satellite maps that enable us to see where and where people are located. 

00:05:22.319 --> 00:05:24.627
 We have this progress in biology 

00:05:24.627 --> 00:05:28.453
 Which should make a tremendous change in the time needed to deal with the virus 

00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:33.602
 We will be able to make medicines and vaccines appropriate for this virus. 

00:05:33.602 --> 00:05:35.288
 So we have tools, 

00:05:35.288 --> 00:05:39.500
 But these tools need to be integrated into the global health system. 

00:05:39.500 --> 00:05:41.793
 And we need to be prepared. 

00:05:41.793 --> 00:05:44.257
 I think the best lessons are how to prepare 

00:05:44.257 --> 00:05:46.758
 It is again, what we do for war. 

